            "Kingdom of Kush (1070 BCE–350 CE) – Nubian kingdom south of Egypt; conquered Egypt in 8th century BCE",
            "Mali Empire (1235–1600 CE) – West African empire; famous for Mansa Musa and trans-Saharan gold and salt trade",
            "Songhai Empire (1464–1591 CE) – largest West African empire; Askia Muhammad expanded it; fell to Moroccan invasion",
            "Great Zimbabwe (11th–15th century) – stone-walled city in southern Africa; centre of gold trade",
